WEBVTT

01:18.754 --> 01:19.215
morning.

01:19.295 --> 01:26.627
It is a joy to be with you this morning and I hope your Father's Day is a great day today from whichever perspective you approach it.

01:26.667 --> 01:36.723
Some of us this morning are blessed to have our dads still with us and we can give them a hug and we can feed them a great dinner and tell them how much we love them so hope today is that day for you.

01:36.803 --> 01:45.938
Others are going to remember and honor a dad who is no longer with them but hope those memories are great and a great time to give thanks to God.

01:46.498 --> 01:53.008
I'm in a latter category and I'll never forget all of the fatherly advice that my dad gave me.

01:54.390 --> 02:02.242
So, you know, dads, I think we kind of all know that dads have a way of being able to, should I say, encourage us in the right way.

02:03.203 --> 02:08.011
My dad could speak the truth and when he spoke, I always knew whether I agreed with him or not.

02:08.591 --> 02:11.977
I knew that he spoke in love and that he spoke in my best interest.

02:12.237 --> 02:15.602
He could say things that other people wouldn't say and he was willing to say things.

02:16.034 --> 02:17.516
that other people wouldn't say.

02:18.377 --> 02:22.262
So with that in mind, I want to begin this morning just looking at a text.

02:22.283 --> 02:30.714
Now, this is not going to be our primary text as we talk about focus, but I do want to look at a text that the apostle Paul gave to Timothy.

02:30.814 --> 02:33.318
Timothy was, in many ways, a protege.

02:33.878 --> 02:34.840
Paul was a mentor.

02:34.940 --> 02:37.663
Paul was like a spiritual dad to Timothy.

02:38.164 --> 02:40.547
And this is in 1 Timothy, chapter 4, verse 16.

02:40.628 --> 02:45.394
Paul says, to Timothy, pay close attention to yourself and to your teaching.

02:46.274 --> 02:52.720
Persevering these things, for as you do this, you will ensure salvation both for yourself and for those who hear you.

02:53.541 --> 03:04.191
I think a lot of times we read this text, we gravitate very quickly and understand the importance, and there is great importance, to this part where he says to Timothy, pay close attention to your teaching.

03:05.292 --> 03:07.794
But this morning, I want to focus on the first part of that.

03:07.834 --> 03:09.055
I don't want to jump over it.

03:09.115 --> 03:16.242
Sometimes we do this part, which sounds like a dad to me when he says, pay close attention to

03:16.386 --> 03:17.007
yourself.

03:18.870 --> 03:22.977
You know, I can't remember how many times my dad said something like that to me.

03:23.017 --> 03:35.860
And I think about it as we think, all of us, about this new season of ministry here at Concord, what God has for us in the part that we play, all of us play in this new season of ministry.

03:36.861 --> 03:41.970
I mean, last week we talked about the fact that we need to focus on our mission.

03:42.050 --> 03:44.834
So at Concord, that means making disciples everywhere.

03:44.874 --> 03:52.726
We talked about how it's important to fix our eyes on Jesus because He can renew our strength to run the race that is set before us.

03:53.788 --> 03:57.073
But this morning, I want to change to the next thing we need to focus on.

03:57.113 --> 04:00.959
That's not our mission, but it's myself.

04:00.979 --> 04:03.543
We don't just need to focus on our mission.

04:03.583 --> 04:10.674
All of us at this season in our life as a church need to focus on ourselves.

04:11.202 --> 04:25.743
When you stop to think about it, the truth is that whether or not we're going to be able to accomplish the mission that Jesus has given us to make disciples everywhere is not really primarily tied to how great our programs are.

04:26.785 --> 04:35.037
I mean, our children's program or our worship program, I mean, these things are important, but that's not what primarily drives our ability to accomplish that mission.

04:35.097 --> 04:38.802
It's not primarily tied to how great the technology is.

04:39.298 --> 04:44.787
or how great the music is on a given Sunday morning, or how great the preacher might be.

04:46.530 --> 05:06.162
The truth is, if we're gonna be able to make disciples everywhere and to transform our region, this is gonna happen because the people that we rub shoulders with, I mean the people we work with, the people we go to school with, the people in our family, can look at us and say, that is a person who is not like everybody else.

05:07.970 --> 05:10.854
I mean, that's a person who is being transformed.

05:12.997 --> 05:19.046
I mean, isn't it true that people when they are being transformed, when they're being changed, when they are thriving?

05:19.086 --> 05:23.733
Isn't it true that those are the people that's hard for them to shut up about it?

05:24.835 --> 05:27.899
People who are being changed to become more like Jesus.

05:29.562 --> 05:34.509
These people are become a powerful force because they are hard to explain away.

05:36.412 --> 05:37.874
They become contagious.

05:39.458 --> 05:46.887
Now, apart from that, if people look at all of us and they do not see people who are being transformed, who are not contagious, what happens then?

05:46.927 --> 05:54.535
When we are people who are stuck in the same place, maybe a bad place, when we are not being transformed.

05:55.697 --> 06:07.410
This morning, I want to talk about this process of focusing on myself, because whether or not I'm being transformed, whether or not we are being transformed, is the primary issue for whether or not we're going to be effective

06:07.778 --> 06:10.622
in accomplishing the mission God has given to all of us.

06:12.125 --> 06:21.018
So when we talk about that, I mean, the truth is if you think about it, doesn't it make sense that if we want to make disciples, that we have to be disciples?

06:22.961 --> 06:23.943
Can't skip that step.

06:23.963 --> 06:24.644
Doesn't it make sense?

06:24.684 --> 06:27.689
The word disciple means to be a learner.

06:29.271 --> 06:32.977
Somebody who's constantly learning from Jesus, who's being transformed by Jesus.

06:32.997 --> 06:34.339
That's the life of a disciple.

06:34.359 --> 06:36.242
If we want to make disciples,

06:37.506 --> 06:41.470
We got to be disciples constantly, all the time.

06:42.311 --> 06:46.916
Now, I'm not here today to say that that type change, transformation, is easy.

06:47.997 --> 06:51.040
And I'm certainly not here today to say that I've got that all figured out.

06:52.422 --> 06:56.526
I mean, I dream of being a better kind of person.

06:57.968 --> 07:03.794
I mean, I dream of being that guy that when somebody pulls out in front of me on the interstate and goes 35 miles an hour,

07:03.874 --> 07:08.521
I dream of being that guy that doesn't want to kill that person in front of me.

07:08.541 --> 07:10.585
I still want to kill that person in front of me.

07:11.226 --> 07:12.047
You may as well.

07:13.449 --> 07:19.399
I dream of being the kind of person who, when it comes to fears and doubts that I just, they just don't even affect me.

07:19.519 --> 07:24.968
I dream of being a person who takes steps of faith constantly and I still got a long way to go.

07:25.228 --> 07:26.310
I don't know what you dream about.

07:27.992 --> 07:31.538
You may be sitting there this morning and saying, why do I still yell at my kids so much?

07:32.994 --> 07:36.358
Why do I still waste so much time doing stupid things?

07:38.801 --> 07:46.190
Or maybe you say, why is this addiction that I've allowed into my life seem to be absolutely undefeatable?

07:49.234 --> 07:52.818
I'm not here to say that change is easy.

07:55.622 --> 07:59.186
But I am here to say that it's possible and that it's possible for you

08:01.922 --> 08:13.038
There's a story in the fifth chapter of John's Gospel where Jesus meets a man by the pool of Bethesda one day and he asks him the most remarkable question when he says, do you want to get well?

08:15.501 --> 08:20.148
He's been in the same condition for 38 years and he has apparently become accustomed to it.

08:20.569 --> 08:24.434
He's lost the hope that anything can be different.

08:25.666 --> 08:32.759
Now, I'm not asking this morning the exact same question that Jesus asked, but I'm going to change the wording a bit and ask a similar question.

08:32.899 --> 08:37.046
I say, do you believe that you can be different?

08:39.551 --> 08:40.372
Because you can.

08:42.315 --> 08:44.058
Change is possible.

08:45.261 --> 08:50.610
It's possible for you, but you just have to understand how it works and where to start.

08:52.098 --> 08:57.544
So let's talk about that this morning, and I want to begin by asking you a simple question, and that is, what is your vision?

08:58.045 --> 09:05.673
When we talk about this subject of spiritual growth or transformation, what's your vision of spiritual growth?

09:08.296 --> 09:20.850
I mean, when some years ago when Deb and I were in another church, I was a pastor in another church, we had some folks who had asked us, they invited us to go skiing with them.

09:21.026 --> 09:26.676
Now, we could never afford to do this ourselves at that particular time, but they asked us to go skiing in Colorado.

09:26.696 --> 09:28.418
I bought the plane tickets, bought the lift tickets.

09:28.438 --> 09:29.260
I mean, just everything.

09:30.362 --> 09:32.565
Took care of us for a whole week, and I'll never forget.

09:32.585 --> 09:38.616
I'll never forget the time when we got to the top of the hill for that first time.

09:39.337 --> 09:44.786
And we looked out on that vista, and we were just in awe.

09:46.018 --> 09:54.030
And it was like at that instant, Debbie and I looked at each other at that moment at the time of that mountain and said, we have got to bring the boys.

09:55.412 --> 10:00.780
At the time, our kids were young, they couldn't have gone anyway at that point in time, and for goodness, we couldn't afford it.

10:02.803 --> 10:04.105
They took us back several times.

10:05.246 --> 10:15.922
And as they did, they gave us this, they kept talking about, you know, you ought to bring your boys out, we just never could do that.

10:16.034 --> 10:18.217
It was out there in the realm of impossibility.

10:18.237 --> 10:20.279
And I don't know when it actually changed.

10:21.040 --> 10:24.024
At some point, something inside of us began to change.

10:25.486 --> 10:29.410
And we began to see this as something that maybe it could happen.

10:29.811 --> 10:33.636
And then one day, a switch flipped.

10:33.656 --> 10:36.819
And we just decided we're going to do it.

10:36.839 --> 10:39.383
And from that moment, we began to look at websites.

10:39.403 --> 10:40.884
We began to compare prices.

10:40.904 --> 10:42.066
We began to look at plane tickets.

10:42.086 --> 10:45.490
It's like suddenly something had changed.

10:45.634 --> 10:47.697
The truth is we talk about spiritual growth.

10:47.717 --> 10:49.941
It always walks that same journey.

10:51.423 --> 10:52.765
It begins as a vision.

10:55.008 --> 10:56.511
It moves to a hope.

10:58.494 --> 11:00.757
And finally, it becomes an intention.

11:01.118 --> 11:05.785
What is your vision when it comes to spiritual growth?

11:07.708 --> 11:11.954
You know, for all of us,

11:12.930 --> 11:14.872
We talk about our vision for spiritual growth.

11:14.952 --> 11:18.896
When I was a kid, I used to think about heaven.

11:20.458 --> 11:21.499
A preacher would preach about it.

11:21.519 --> 11:25.283
My vision about heaven was an eternal church service.

11:25.423 --> 11:27.165
That's what my thought about heaven was.

11:27.686 --> 11:31.290
I mean, it's like in my mind, it was like heaven meant you're gonna go there.

11:31.330 --> 11:34.113
Everybody's gonna be wearing choir robes for all eternity.

11:34.493 --> 11:35.835
And we're all gonna be singing songs.

11:35.855 --> 11:38.237
Let's do a long boring sermon for all eternity.

11:38.297 --> 11:42.642
And can I just say to you, I was not all that motivated to go to heaven.

11:43.522 --> 11:44.663
Because my vision went wrong.

11:47.147 --> 11:49.690
What's your vision for spiritual growth?

11:51.272 --> 11:54.476
Is it just to become more rule focused?

11:55.558 --> 11:56.179
Is that your vision?

11:58.882 --> 12:04.590
When we talk about spiritual growth, the transformation, is it just to become more predictable?

12:05.751 --> 12:07.954
Is it just to become somebody who just has to

12:08.098 --> 12:11.942
Give up everything you love so that you can have something in heaven one day.

12:12.022 --> 12:13.104
Is that the whole process?

12:13.144 --> 12:16.708
This lifetime of giving up everything that you love?

12:16.728 --> 12:18.270
Is that all that's involved in it?

12:19.211 --> 12:21.814
What's your vision for spiritual growth?

12:24.196 --> 12:28.862
You know, when we talk about this subject, one of my favorite books is a book by a guy named John Ortberg.

12:30.564 --> 12:32.626
It's called The Life You Always Wanted.

12:33.922 --> 12:37.406
And in it, he tells a story about a friend of his named Tom Schmidt.

12:37.446 --> 12:40.910
Tom was visiting a nursing home, not a father's day, but it was on a mother's day.

12:40.930 --> 12:44.294
And he had roses he's going to give to each of the residents.

12:46.177 --> 12:54.927
And as he walked down the halls of this particular nursing home, he went down one hall that had patients on it that were really a little more extreme.

12:54.947 --> 12:59.333
And he came up on a lady, he found out later, her name was Mabel.

13:01.035 --> 13:03.858
And the polite way to say it is that Mabel was

13:04.098 --> 13:32.594
grotesque found out later that the administrators of the nursing home when they had a new employee and they wanted to find out is this person going to be able to make it they would send them to feed Mabel because they figured that if they could stand the site of that they could stand anything else in the building so Tom walks up to this lady named Mabel on this particular day and he hands her a flower she puts it up to her face to smell it but she can't smell any more and so

13:32.866 --> 13:34.468
She says, can I give it to somebody else?

13:34.488 --> 13:35.510
She says, sure.

13:35.530 --> 13:40.197
And she poked it out to the lady next to her and says, here, this is from Jesus.

13:43.001 --> 13:46.526
She said, at that moment, I realized this is not a normal person.

13:47.948 --> 13:51.433
Found out later that Mabel had been raised on a small farm.

13:52.975 --> 13:55.879
She stayed there until her mom and dad had both died.

13:55.939 --> 14:00.786
After which time she lost her sight, she began to get sick.

14:01.314 --> 14:09.065
She'd been placed in this particular nursing home 25 years ago and all these 25 years she has been getting weaker and sicker.

14:10.067 --> 14:16.135
She lives in a room with three patients who scream constantly and cannot engage her in conversation.

14:19.580 --> 14:21.123
Sort of like hell on earth.

14:23.726 --> 14:29.074
He goes back to visit her every couple of weeks along with a lot of the other patients.

14:30.146 --> 14:36.034
And as he sits in Mabel's room, they became friends and he would read scripture to her.

14:38.738 --> 14:43.044
And he realized that every time he stopped, she would continue word for word.

14:45.207 --> 14:50.654
And they would sing hymns together and she would stop him from time to time and comment on the meaning.

14:53.438 --> 14:59.026
He began to shift from being just someone who pitied her to someone who she was like a thing of wonder to him.

15:00.482 --> 15:01.924
how someone could do this.

15:01.944 --> 15:14.183
I mean, here's someone who has somehow tapped into a supernatural power to overcome awful things, things that would make all of us bitter and mean.

15:14.243 --> 15:26.322
He asked her one day, says, maybe what do you think about in this room, locked in this room with these vegetables?

15:28.258 --> 15:33.245
Not able to tell if it's day or night, and she says, I think about Jesus, I think about how good he's been to me.

15:38.854 --> 15:39.955
She had been changed.

15:42.319 --> 15:47.687
I just need to ask you this morning, is that your vision to be changed inwardly?

15:48.208 --> 15:57.842
Because when we talk about Jesus' vision for you and for me, Jesus is not envisioning that you're just gonna become more rule-centered

15:57.986 --> 16:01.130
or better able to meet somebody else's expectations.

16:01.671 --> 16:03.933
In the seventh chapter of John's gospel.

16:06.036 --> 16:06.457
There you go.

16:08.619 --> 16:10.642
There you go, seventh chapter of John's gospel.

16:11.523 --> 16:15.348
Jesus talks about the impact of the Holy Spirit in your life and mine.

16:16.269 --> 16:17.470
And here's how he describes it.

16:17.511 --> 16:20.695
He says, if any man is thirsty, let him come to me and drink.

16:21.556 --> 16:26.642
He who believes in me out of his innermost being shall flow

16:27.170 --> 16:29.835
rivers of living water.

16:31.057 --> 16:36.968
Now listen to this, this is not something that is imposed on you from outside.

16:37.008 --> 16:45.383
The text says, it flows out of your innermost being, something inside of your innermost being.

16:45.403 --> 16:51.794
The King James says, out of his belly shall flow rivers of living water.

16:52.066 --> 16:54.229
It's not imposed on you from outside.

16:54.469 --> 16:58.094
You have become fundamentally a different kind of person.

16:58.856 --> 17:01.519
It's not something that flickers on once in a while.

17:01.579 --> 17:04.103
It's the Bible describes it as a flow.

17:04.143 --> 17:09.691
And it's not something that's meager or just barely enough to get by and survive.

17:09.991 --> 17:20.466
Jesus says it is like a river out of his innermost being shall flow rivers of living water.

17:21.314 --> 17:22.796
Is this what you've envisioned?

17:24.299 --> 17:29.026
Is this what you're aiming for, hoping for, intending to see happen?

17:29.808 --> 17:30.970
Because it can happen.

17:33.233 --> 17:41.266
Listen, Jesus is talking about you becoming a fundamentally different kind of person, a process that changed you from the

17:41.378 --> 17:46.083
inside so that somewhere in the depth of your soul, you know you're a different person.

17:46.383 --> 17:49.767
You see with different eyes, you want different things.

17:49.807 --> 17:54.371
The things you used to be afraid of losing don't even matter to you anymore.

17:54.632 --> 17:58.275
And you act with completely different motivations.

18:00.277 --> 18:04.882
Is that your vision?

18:04.902 --> 18:08.626
And let me say, have you made that your intention?

18:11.714 --> 18:12.675
Is that your intention?

18:13.316 --> 18:17.340
Because as I said a minute ago, all change, all spiritual change.

18:17.380 --> 18:21.404
Yes, spiritual change is unique in the sense that the Holy Spirit is involved in this.

18:21.824 --> 18:23.506
He's the one who triggers the desire.

18:23.746 --> 18:25.048
He's the one that gives you power.

18:25.088 --> 18:28.091
But on the human side, we cooperate with him.

18:29.392 --> 18:32.275
And that part of the equation is exactly the same.

18:33.316 --> 18:38.962
It moves from a vision to a hope to finally an intention.

18:39.650 --> 18:42.954
And I just need to ask you this morning, have you made this your intention?

18:45.497 --> 18:52.707
Listen, transformation can happen for you, but it's not gonna happen like catching the flu.

18:55.450 --> 18:57.593
It's gonna happen the same way all change happens.

18:58.314 --> 19:04.141
It moves from vision to hope to intention.

19:04.161 --> 19:05.603
You can make this your intention.

19:07.425 --> 19:08.146
Let me tell you how.

19:10.050 --> 19:12.153
It moves from inward and inward change.

19:13.374 --> 19:15.357
Vision to hope to intention.

19:15.377 --> 19:19.903
That's all inward to finally begin to work at outward in your life.

19:20.664 --> 19:26.552
And you do this first by reprogramming the way that you think.

19:26.572 --> 19:29.456
Now I'm not a pilot, but I love airplanes.

19:30.397 --> 19:33.341
And whenever I've had an opportunity, somebody is a pilot, they invite me to go.

19:33.401 --> 19:34.643
I mean, I'm there.

19:35.564 --> 19:40.050
So I get a chance to learn some about how these things work and, you know, buddy of mine who used to

19:40.226 --> 19:43.169
have a plane would take me to show me how the navigation systems work.

19:43.189 --> 19:54.781
And he'd show me how the autopilot system work and how in an airplane, if you program it on a certain heading, I mean, it is going to fly that heading because it's programmed to fly that heading.

19:56.402 --> 19:58.524
Now you can make it go somewhere different.

19:59.986 --> 20:07.954
If you were to take the yoke and turn it and hold it there manually, you can make it go somewhere different.

20:09.058 --> 20:12.382
but only as long as you hold the yoke in that spot.

20:14.104 --> 20:24.817
The minute your arms get tired or the minute you get distracted, you let go and it reverts to its programming immediately.

20:26.940 --> 20:29.803
You know, a lot of people live their Christian life like that.

20:30.744 --> 20:38.834
They think it's just an overdose of willpower and they do it that way for a while until they get tired

20:38.978 --> 20:43.083
They get distracted and they let go of the yoke.

20:44.725 --> 20:46.607
And then their programming takes over.

20:49.450 --> 20:51.352
Listen, you can change your programming.

20:51.993 --> 20:55.297
You can learn to think the way that God thinks.

20:58.000 --> 21:03.546
It won't happen by accident, but you can make this happen.

21:04.127 --> 21:06.770
Paul talks about in Romans the 12th chapter.

21:07.138 --> 21:12.864
He says, do not be conformed this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind.

21:15.026 --> 21:28.039
And what we're talking about here is saturating yourself with the Word of God until you begin to think, program your mind, think like God thinks.

21:28.059 --> 21:30.841
Now listen, this coming to church is great.

21:32.963 --> 21:34.425
Coming to church is a wonderful thing.

21:34.485 --> 21:35.666
I'm glad you're here today.

21:37.410 --> 21:43.757
But it won't saturate one time a week, one hour a week, won't saturate you with the Word of God.

21:47.461 --> 21:49.924
Having a 90-second devotion every morning.

21:50.525 --> 21:50.765
Why?

21:50.865 --> 21:51.466
That's great.

21:52.747 --> 21:53.228
Keep doing it.

21:54.429 --> 21:55.550
You might want to extend it a little.

21:56.872 --> 22:00.215
But 90 seconds a day won't saturate you.

22:00.295 --> 22:01.917
It won't reprogram your mind.

22:03.619 --> 22:06.162
You can reprogram your mind.

22:09.538 --> 22:18.029
You can hear what God says, read what God says, study what God says, memorize what God says, make this a part of your everyday life all day.

22:18.850 --> 22:24.458
Listen, I read someplace not long ago where Americans watch something like four hours of television a day.

22:25.940 --> 22:34.191
And if you do the math, that's about in a 65 year life, that's about nine years of staring at a television screen.

22:36.114 --> 22:37.956
It doesn't even include the other screen time.

22:38.176 --> 22:39.378
Do you realize

22:39.490 --> 22:43.434
that every one of those programmers has an agenda.

22:45.976 --> 22:48.779
Every one of those movies you watch, every one of those shows you watch.

22:49.319 --> 22:50.080
I do it as well.

22:50.120 --> 22:52.362
We all, I mean, I'm not saying it's wrong to watch anything.

22:52.382 --> 22:53.483
I'm just gonna be discerning.

22:55.766 --> 23:00.370
Because everything you're exposed to is programming your mind one way or the other.

23:00.390 --> 23:08.818
90 seconds a day won't over, it won't counteract everything the world's trying to give you or teach you.

23:09.986 --> 23:11.287
or implant in you.

23:13.209 --> 23:14.010
It takes more than that.

23:16.412 --> 23:17.493
Reprogram your mind.

23:18.574 --> 23:22.218
You're not be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind.

23:24.660 --> 23:27.743
You can also replace trying with training.

23:29.925 --> 23:31.146
Now, I love to hike.

23:32.567 --> 23:39.634
If you ask me today to go hike someplace, I mean, five miles, 10 miles, hey, I'm great with that.

23:39.938 --> 23:43.021
No problem.

23:43.041 --> 23:50.168
But if you ask me today to run a marathon, I mean, not walking, but running.

23:50.709 --> 23:52.070
And not five and 10 miles, but what?

23:52.090 --> 23:52.891
24 miles?

23:52.911 --> 23:53.332
What is it?

23:53.352 --> 23:57.476
24.2 miles, something like that?

23:57.516 --> 23:59.558
Six miles.

23:59.578 --> 23:59.678
26.2.

23:59.698 --> 24:02.841
If you ask me today to run a marathon, I cannot.

24:06.064 --> 24:07.666
It don't matter how hard I try.

24:09.858 --> 24:10.238
You get me?

24:12.861 --> 24:13.822
I'll have a heart attack.

24:14.823 --> 24:15.684
I'll fall over and die.

24:16.064 --> 24:21.069
I do not possess the ability to do it by trying.

24:24.833 --> 24:25.774
But I can train for it.

24:30.118 --> 24:33.241
I mean, old and decrepit as I am, I can train for that.

24:33.261 --> 24:36.605
You give me six months with a precise training process.

24:36.765 --> 24:37.906
I can run a marathon.

24:39.266 --> 24:50.699
Some of us need to replace our paradigm, and we need to realize that becoming like Jesus is not a matter of just trying harder, but it is something that we can train for.

24:52.502 --> 25:06.578
Scientists tell us that every time you dribble a basketball, every time you play a piece of music, that there is a neural pathway physically created in your brain.

25:07.906 --> 25:14.076
Now at first it's pretty weak, which is why we feel really awkward when we're trying to learn a skill for the first time.

25:15.478 --> 25:22.609
But every time you repeat that action, you dribble that basketball, you play that piece of music, that neural pathway becomes more stable.

25:23.511 --> 25:28.659
That is, it's initially, imagine like a rickety rope bridge, maybe over a river.

25:29.560 --> 25:33.106
Every time you repeat that action in the right way.

25:33.730 --> 25:36.993
that rope bridge becomes then a wooden bridge.

25:37.034 --> 25:39.416
And finally, then it is a stone bridge.

25:39.436 --> 25:50.388
And one day it is a concrete and steel super highway, which is why when we're learning new skills, we all experience it the same way.

25:50.448 --> 25:52.570
It starts out we say, I could never do that.

25:54.052 --> 25:58.716
And then one day we say, well, maybe I could do that.

25:58.736 --> 26:00.178
And then I can do that.

26:01.250 --> 26:03.974
And then we finally say, why doesn't everybody do that?

26:03.994 --> 26:05.276
It's so natural for us.

26:06.278 --> 26:11.306
This is why athletes and musicians, you know, no athlete loves to do the drills.

26:12.388 --> 26:15.953
But something about these drills that they do remakes them internally.

26:16.414 --> 26:17.816
It changes their reflexes.

26:18.357 --> 26:21.062
Musicians don't live to play scales.

26:22.624 --> 26:26.891
But when they play those scales, it rewires them internally.

26:26.931 --> 26:28.914
It makes new reflexes.

26:31.010 --> 26:33.834
The same principle applies to you and me.

26:35.737 --> 26:48.935
The physical change also to spiritual change, how we are reflexes in terms of how we respond to situations, how we attitudes we are natural to us or actions that we take.

26:49.536 --> 26:56.826
Christians have known for years that there are drills that remake us inwardly and create new reflexes.

26:56.846 --> 26:59.410
These are called spiritual disciplines.

27:00.674 --> 27:24.114
Listen, the habit of giving, which is one of the ways we need to become like Jesus to be generous, is not going to appear in you magically out of thin air, but it becomes real in you and me when we practice it.

27:26.018 --> 27:27.481
You can practice a hundred things.

27:27.521 --> 27:30.326
You can practice the grace of God by forgiving people.

27:30.386 --> 27:37.298
You can practice generosity to become like Jesus by giving in a regular way.

27:37.318 --> 27:43.849
You can practice growing your faith by obedience in small things so that one day obedience in bigger things is natural to you.

27:43.970 --> 27:46.514
You can practice serving others, which is

27:46.722 --> 27:53.409
what it means to become like Jesus to be humble until it's more natural for you can practice self-control about something like fasting.

27:53.429 --> 27:55.170
There are a hundred ways you can do this.

27:55.531 --> 28:01.277
You may need to pick one today to be intentional.

28:05.701 --> 28:07.863
We renew the way we think.

28:08.344 --> 28:10.346
We replace trying with training.

28:11.367 --> 28:14.610
You know, Peter says with this process of

28:15.266 --> 28:20.292
of reinforcing ourselves that works in the positive direction, also works in the negative direction.

28:20.312 --> 28:24.618
He says, I urge you as aliens and strangers abstain from fleshly lust, why?

28:25.298 --> 28:27.761
Because they wage war against the soul.

28:28.062 --> 28:34.209
Every time I give in to what the Bible calls fleshly lust, I'm reinforcing the wrong things.

28:35.771 --> 28:36.652
You don't have to do that.

28:38.194 --> 28:44.402
You can reinforce the right things until they're natural for you, normal for you.

28:45.634 --> 29:00.638
you're becoming like Jesus, reprogram your mind, replace trying with training, and then cultivate life-changing relationships, or be selective about the people you hang out with.

29:03.683 --> 29:13.458
You know, scientists tell us, social scientists tell us that, and we've all seen it, you know, sit in a circle with people, you know, and one person just yawns, like that.

29:14.498 --> 29:15.921
And within a minute, you ever seen this?

29:16.001 --> 29:18.726
Everybody around the circle is somehow yawning, and why is that?

29:22.173 --> 29:25.539
One person stands there and they're talking, and there's two people, and he crosses his arms.

29:25.559 --> 29:33.014
And the guy who's over there next to him, some reason he crosses his arms, too, why is that?

29:33.034 --> 29:35.378
Social scientists call that mimicking.

29:39.266 --> 29:41.068
It's a powerful thing.

29:41.168 --> 29:46.093
We're not aware of it, but even in things that are incidental and unimportant, we mimic each other.

29:46.113 --> 29:47.534
We're affected by each other.

29:49.536 --> 30:02.610
Now, you better believe that if it's true in things that are incidental and unimportant, it's also true about things that are supremely important.

30:02.630 --> 30:06.834
Proverbs 13, verse 20 says, he who walks with wise men will be wise.

30:08.962 --> 30:11.105
Companion of fools will suffer harm.

30:11.526 --> 30:20.518
Listen, speak especially to young people this morning, but this is applicable to all of us.

30:20.799 --> 30:29.351
If you want to become like Jesus, and you can, you can be transformed.

30:29.871 --> 30:37.362
Listen, the most important and powerful influencers in your life are not gonna be a book you read

30:39.138 --> 30:46.628
or a sermon you heard, they're going to be the people you choose to spend time with.

30:49.753 --> 30:55.401
If you want to become like Jesus, then hang out with people who remind you of Jesus.

30:59.607 --> 31:00.328
How simple is that?

31:02.150 --> 31:07.698
If you want to become like Jesus, hang out with people who remind you of Jesus.

31:12.258 --> 31:12.819
Find a group.

31:16.723 --> 31:23.770
Get together with some guys in a no sweat group or an accountability group, but find people who remind you of Jesus.

31:23.830 --> 31:26.774
They become the most powerful influences in your life.

31:30.377 --> 31:31.358
Where do you need to start?

31:32.820 --> 31:36.944
Because listen, unless we are disciples, we can't make disciples.

31:38.466 --> 31:42.130
To be a disciple means to be transformed constantly all the time.

31:43.042 --> 31:51.754
to subject myself to the influence of the Holy Spirit so that out of my innermost being, rivers of living water are beginning to flow.

31:51.774 --> 31:52.896
It's a powerful thing.

31:55.680 --> 31:56.601
And it can be true for you.

31:59.565 --> 32:01.228
Let me ask you to bow your heads and close your eyes.

32:05.474 --> 32:06.495
So where do you need to start?

32:07.977 --> 32:11.282
To be intentional about change.

32:12.834 --> 32:23.746
Not to leave it to chance, but to cooperate with the Holy Spirit so that the power that Jesus is talking about becomes absolutely real in you.

32:27.110 --> 32:31.755
You may need to start with one of these spiritual disciplines to be intentional.

32:33.337 --> 32:38.322
You may need to start by choosing and be more selective about the people you hang out with.

32:41.538 --> 32:44.983
You may need to reprogram your mind with the Word of God.

32:47.427 --> 32:48.990
Saturate yourself with the Word of God.

32:49.110 --> 32:52.155
Father, thank You for the truth of Your Word.

32:52.976 --> 32:54.739
Give us grace to know where we should begin.

32:54.759 --> 32:58.705
And Father, use us as Your instruments.

32:58.745 --> 33:00.388
We pray in Jesus' name.

33:01.370 --> 33:01.650
Amen.

